&ldquo;People who enjoy meetings should not be in charge of anything.&rdquo; —Thomas Sowell
 I hate meetings. I hate meetings as much as I hate religious people. Well, research from Harvard Business School &amp; London school of Economics shows;
Top executives spend upwards of 18 hours per week - third of their working week - in meetings. Estimated 25-50% of meeting time considered wasted Research shows the cost of Unnecessary meeting to Business in terms of wasted salary hours as $37 Billion.
